            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "It does indeed also affect `gx`. Makes that also unusable.\r\n\r\n> Is there a way we can make it work with vim.wait() ?\r\n\r\nThere simply shouldn't be a wait for the caller.\r\n\r\nI suggest we return the task object itself. The caller can then still decide to wait if they really want to,\r\nbut in probably 99% of the cases, you don't want to wait for a running GUI application\r\n",
